{meta: title I Cried But My Tears Were Too Late}
{meta: artist Hank Snow}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]One heart too many I have [G7]broken love dreams that faded and [C]died
[G7]Too many teardrops [D7]have fallen  too many vows cast [G7]aside
[C]Soft wedding bells should be ringing for us [G7]in the chapel [C]tonight
[F]But this morning they tolled and her bright band of [C]gold
[D7]Was returned with this message [G7]tonight
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[C]Your sweetheart has left us [G7]today
[C]Heart broken God took her away
[F]That silk gown of white for her wedding [C]tonight
[D7]She wore as they laid her [G7]away
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[C]Though she died for a love all in [G7]vain
[C]Her last words were calling your name
[F]As I walked to her grave where the bluebonnets wave
[C]I cried but my [G7]tears were too [C]late
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
Spoken:
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
Tonight sweetheart as I kneel here alone beside you
And my tears stain the flowers on your grave
In deep regret I think of the heart that I have wounded
Of the sorrow and grief and the life that I could have saved
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
Yes tonight darling you were to be my loving bride
But all that I have left now as I bow to pray
Is your ring a picture the sad message that they sent me
And this rose that I am taking from your grave
{end_of_verse}

